50|$|In {{the late}} Middle Ages, the minting house cooperatives {{vanished}} when minting {{was taken over}} by sovereigns or cities. The Münzmeister was now an entrepreneur who determined weight, precious-metal content, <b>seignorage</b> and their own share, by way of free negotiations with the principals. Next to mines and shipyards, mints had become the largest enterprises of the age.|$|E
