50|$|Some small {{countries}} such as El Salvador, Ecuador and Montenegro have unilaterally adopted {{the use of a}} more stable foreign currency as a means of controlling inflation. The cost of this is generally very high, as the adopting country loses all control over monetary policy, and all the benefits of <b>seignorage.</b> A currency board is a second tier solution, where the exchange rate of the currency is fixed to that of another country, or a basket of currencies.|$|E
